                        Citizen survey shows satisfied users, but public services have room for improvement, minister says
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[Press release, Ministry of Government Administration, Reform and Church Affairs, 14.01.2010]</p>
                <p>86 per cent of the citizens of Norway think that their country is close to being a perfect country to live in. We are also satisfied with public services. These are conclusions from the nationwide Citizen Survey which measures how satisfied Norwegian citizens are with municipal, regional and government services. </p>
                
                
